org.apache.arrow.vector.complex

Interface RepeatedValueVector

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, Iterable<ValueVector>, ValueVector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseRepeatedValueVector, ListVector

    public interface RepeatedValueVector
extends ValueVector
    An abstraction representing repeated value vectors. A repeated vector contains values that may either be flat or nested. A value consists of zero or more cells(inner values). Current design maintains data and offsets vectors. Each cell is stored in the data vector. Repeated vector uses the offset vector to determine the sequence of cells pertaining to an individual value.
